('https://jobs.mayoclinic.org/diversity', 175801, 3, 'Thread40', 175384, '2022-04-23 07:02:55', 1, 'Diversity, equity, and inclusion are integral to Mayo Clinic s mission. Learn More.', '[life-changing careers, search by role or keyword, enter location, , diversity, equity, and inclusion are integral to mayo clinic\'s mission to provide excellent, culturally relevant care in a welcoming environment to patients from a wide variety of backgrounds and create an inclusive work environment where differences are valued, allowing individuals to achieve and contribute to their fullest potential. this commitment to diversity, equity, and inclusion is woven into the fabric of mayo clinic—we embrace these values as we serve our patients, employees, students, suppliers, and communities., mayo clinic has been named to diversityinc\'s 2020 top specialty list for hospitals and health systems ranking. the diversityinc survey assesses how u.s. companies with more than 1,000 staff members manage diversity., mayo clinics in arizona, florida, and rochester have been recognized by the human rights campaign foundation as \"leaders in lgbtq healthcare equality.\" the human rights campaign foundation is the educational arm of the human rights campaign, the largest civil rights organization in the u.s. working to achieve equality for lesbian, gay, bisexual, transgender, and queer (lgbtq) people., mayo clinic has been named a 2022 \"military-friendly employer\" by military friendly®. the organization measures an employer\'s commitment, effort, and success in creating sustainable and meaningful practices and opportunities for people in the military community, including active-duty, national guard, reserve, military spouses and veterans. mayo clinic was recognized as follows: military-friendly employer (bronze designation), military spouse-friendly employer, military-friendly supplier diversity program (ranked no. 7), and military-friendly brand (ranked no. 5)., we’re proud to work with some excellent organizations to promote diversity and inclusion, both at mayo clinic and in our communities., mayo clinic works with aises to increase representation of american indians, alaska natives, native hawaiians, pacific islanders, first nations, and other indigenous peoples of north america in science, technology, engineering, and math (stem) studies and careers at mayo clinic., mayo clinic partners with the nbmbaa to foster mutually beneficial relationships that offer resources and career opportunities for african americans and diverse business professionals., mayo clinic partners with prospanica to empower and enable hispanic professionals to find life-long careers., mayo clinic, in collaboration with the u.s. department of defense (dod), provides military service members who are within 180 days of separation from military service with internship opportunities in a variety of different roles. this allows service members to learn and train in mayo clinic’s world-class environment as they prepare to transition to the civilian sector., hear from our employees as they share their stories of diversity, inclusion, and belonging., mayo clinic — lgbti, the lgbti mayo employee resource group (merg), in partnership with the workforce development and the office of equity, inclusion, and diversity, share why they feel a sense of belonging at mayo clinic and choose to build their careers here. listen to mayo clinic employees share why our values create a sense of community, support inclusivity, and encourage everyone to bring their authentic selves to work to best serve our patients., mayo clinic — inclusion, the disability mayo employee resource group (merg), in partnership with the office of equity, inclusion, and diversity, recently launched a self-id campaign. mayo clinic continually strives to improve inclusiveness and support the success of all staff. participating in the self-id campaign will create a culture of safety for all to bring their best self to work. disabi