id-19 cases using a bayesian statistical model — named for english mathematician thomas bayes. this model automatically updates predictions over time, as new data is available., mayo clinic uses a bayesian susceptible, infected, recovered (sir) model. our model parameters are updated with daily case counts every day and then use 500 simulations to produce a median forecast and 95% uncertainty interval for future cases. the infection rate used in this prediction model can vary across locations and time, due to the impact of changes in public behavior and different sars-cov-2 strains., look two weeks into the future with our precise prediction model., the cdc recommends additional doses and booster doses of covid-19 vaccines in specific instances. these include booster doses for everyone age 12 and older who received both doses of the pfizer-biontech covid-19, everyone age 18 and older who received the moderna covid-19 vaccine, as well as those who are 18 and older who had a janssen/johnson & johnson covid-19 vaccine. people who have a moderately or severely weakened immune system should get an additional primary dose and a booster dose., the delta (b.1.617.2) variant is nearly twice as contagious as earlier variants and might cause more severe illness. the omicron (b.1.1.529) variant spreads more easily than the original virus that causes covid-19 and the delta variant. however, omicron appears to cause less severe disease., while research suggests that covid-19 vaccines are slightly less effective against the variants, the vaccines still appear to provide protection against severe covid-19., rolling up your sleeve for a covid-19 shot offers many benefits to you and the people you love:, the safety of covid-19 vaccines has been studied extensively, and adverse effects such as serious allergic reactions are rare. these vaccines were approved quickly because the red tape was cut — not corners. watch this explanation of how covid-19 vaccines were created so quickly by a