ell, or behave as well. further, poor sleep quality makes children more vulnerable to anxiety and depression.  and anxiety is a major cause of sleeplessness. so it can become a vicious cycle. the bottom line is that the body needs to rest, rejuvenate and restore its physical and chemical properties in order to function well. prioritizing sleep quality is essential to health. it’s just as important as diet and exercise. give your family the opportunity to sleep by providing an environment and a bedtime routine that is sleep-promoting. keep the […], receive stories and resources like these in your inbox!, about nemours, when you have questions about your child’s health, you want answers you can trust. nemours children’s health system is here with those answers — and so much more., for decades, nemours has been home to some of the top doctors and specialists in their fields. now, we’re here to bring that caring and comprehensive expertise to you. count on us for up-to-date insights on important topics in kids’ health., navigate, © 2022 the nemours foundation.® nemours is a registered trademark of the nemours foundation.]', 'to mask or not to mask? good question. - nemours blog', '[to mask or not to mask? good question., look at the numbers, what if a child is worried about being teased?, subscribe to our blog, subscribe to our blog, topics, better health is a journey, better health is a journey, related articles, we’ll get through this together: wear your mask and stay apart, this year’s back-to-school fashion includes a face mask, the pandemic can disrupt a good night’s sleep too, subscribe to our blog, subscribe to our blog, topics, subscribe to our blog, topics]', '[, blog nemours blog, , , coronavirus, ages & stages, health issues, staying healthy, , , coronavirus, ages & stages, health issues, staying healthy, contact us, subscribe, nemours, , subscribe, topics ages & stages community connection coronavirus featured post health issues positive parenting services &