equently rushed home. his fiancee and daughters lillie saint, two, and piper rose, one next month, have gone to a safe house while maguire himself is staying with a team-mate, the report adds., chris wheeler: interim manager ralf rangnick confirmed pogba is set to miss the rest of the season and expects united\'s £89million record signing to leave for nothing when his contract runs out., exclusive interview by ian ladyman: rob page page has taken wales to euro 2020 and on the brink of a first world cup appearance despite being a caretaker manager., chris wheeler: much to his frustration, ralf rangnick has not had the kind of impact at manchester united he would have wanted since replacing ole gunnar solskjaer., arsenal are currently the favourites to sign gabriel jesus and the man city striker is open to the move, according to reports., the italian government is considering banning russian and belarusian players from the prestigious italian open as the fallout to the wimbledon decision continues., tyson fury and dillian whyte will go toe-to-toe in their world heavyweight title bout in front of a record crowd for a boxing bout in britain at wembley stadium., exclusive interview by riath al-samarrai: from white spots to yellow dots, the broken giant is drawing an awful line. for two hours he has been looking at his old life and the new, at what has gone and what might be next to go. he knows the robberies won\'t stop until there is nothing left to take. and so steve thompson sits for a while in silence in this lovely pub in cheshire. in his hand is his phone and a picture of what it all cost, which is why he is shaking that damaged head with the scars and mangled ears. \'look at this,\' he says, flicking to a top-down scan of his brain. \'the doctor said if you\'ve got a pinprick of yellow, that\'s a significant brain injury. whatever is yellow is dead.\', exclusive: channel 4 has won the battle to broadcast england\'s nations league matches this summer., the fa have 